{
  "texts": [
    "c A heralded single photon source is used.",
    "FPC: fiber polarization controller; Col.: collimator; SLM: spatial light modulator; L1-L6: lenses; BS: beam splitter; Cam.",
    ": camera; SPD1&2: single photon detector; C.C.",
    ": coincidence counting; PPLN1&2: periodically poled lithium niobate; SHG: second harmonic generation; SPDC: spontaneous parametric down-conversion; BPF: bandpass filter.",
    "While the heralding photons of the photon pairs are sent to the SPD1, the heralded photons are prepared into input states by complex modulation using SLM1, followed by D 2 NN-generated phase layers loaded onto SLM2 to perform the desired operation."
  ]
}